Add platform-bus NIC support for VPP via AF_XDP on NXP DPAA1 FMan.

NXP DPAA1 FMan Ethernet NICs (driver: fsl_dpa) are on the platform bus,
not PCI. At boot ALL ports (eth0-eth4) are owned by the kernel via:
  fsl_dpaa_mac  — MAC hardware control (PHY, link state)
  fsl_dpa       — Linux netdev (creates ethN)

DPDK DPAA PMD is BLOCKED for mixed kernel+VPP mode (RC#31): dpaa_bus
probe initializes ALL BMan/QMan hardware globally, killing kernel-managed
interfaces within seconds. AF_XDP is the only viable path for mixed mode
(~3.5 Gbps on 10G SFP+).

This patch enables VPP to use AF_XDP on selected DPAA1 ports when the
user configures them with 'set vpp settings interface ethX':

1. Adds fsl_dpa to SUPPORTED_DRIVERS and not_pci_drv lists
2. DPAA1 interfaces (fsl_dpa) use driver='xdp' — AF_XDP works WITH the
   kernel driver, no unbind needed, no RC#31 bus conflict
3. PCI NICs continue to use driver='dpdk' as before
4. Injects original_driver into iface_config for template use
5. Injects default xdp_options (rx_queue_size=4096, tx_queue_size=4096,
   num_rx_queues=1) when not provided by CLI for fsl_dpa interfaces
6. startup.conf.j2: enables af_xdp_plugin.so, keeps dpdk {} block for
   PCI NICs only (DPAA interfaces use VPP's host-interface AF_XDP path)
7. Lowers resource minimums for embedded ARM64 boards (2 CPUs, 256M heap)
8. Removes SSE4.2 CPU check (irrelevant on ARM64)

DPAA1 XDP MTU constraint: fsl_dpaa_mac enforces max MTU 3290 for XDP.
AF_XDP socket creation fails with EINVAL if MTU exceeds 3290. SFP+ ports
under VPP are limited to ~3304-byte max frame (3290 + 14 Ethernet header).

Port ownership lifecycle (AF_XDP — no unbind/rebind needed):
  boot               → all eth0-eth4 under kernel (fsl_dpa creates netdevs)
  set vpp ... eth3   → VPP creates AF_XDP socket on eth3 (kernel keeps netdev)
  delete vpp ... eth3→ VPP releases AF_XDP socket, kernel retains full control

Tested on NXP LS1046A Mono Gateway with VPP v25.10.0-48 AF_XDP on
eth3/eth4 (10G SFP+).

